kind of troubling news

00:01:22.620 --> 00:01:25.140 align:middle line:90%
that has surfaced recently.

00:01:25.140 --> 00:01:28.590 align:middle line:84%
And I think a lot of it has
to do with young people whose

00:01:28.590 --> 00:01:31.090 align:middle line:90%
world has become deconstructed.

00:01:31.090 --> 00:01:33.460 align:middle line:84%
They're not going to
class, a lot of them

00:01:33.460 --> 00:01:35.610 align:middle line:84%
they're not interacting
with each other.

00:01:35.610 --> 00:01:36.840 align:middle line:90%
And this was what came up.

00:01:36.840 --> 00:01:40.500 align:middle line:84%
One in four Americans
between the age of 18 to 25

00:01:40.500 --> 00:01:46.350 align:middle line:84%
in a recent study have
seriously contemplated suicide.

00:01:46.350 --> 00:01:48.430 align:middle line:90%
Those are not normal numbers.

00:01:48.430 --> 00:01:51.510 align:middle line:84%
But here we are, and you
have a massive clientele.

00:01:51.510 --> 00:01:54.250 align:middle line:90%
Emotion code is globally.

00:01:54.250 --> 00:01:55.830 align:middle line:84%
So first of all, I
wanted to find out

00:01:55.830 --> 00:01:59.370 align:middle line:84%
from you, what kind
of urgency or shift

00:01:59.370 --> 00:02:02.985 align:middle line:84%
of your practitioners-- what
about 5,000 of them now?

00:02:02.985 --> 00:02:04.110 align:middle line:90%
>> NELSON: We've got 7,000.

00:02:04.110 --> 00:02:04.515 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: 7,000.

00:02:04.515 --> 00:02:05.350 align:middle line:90%
I'm behind.

00:02:05.350 --> 00:02:06.870 align:middle line:90%
That was last time we talked.

00:02:06.870 --> 00:02:09.690 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:02:09.690 --> 00:02:13.080 align:middle line:84%
You've been getting feedback
as the center of all of it.

00:02:13.080 --> 00:02:17.400 align:middle line:84%
What has happened since the
world's events have changed

00:02:17.400 --> 00:02:20.490 align:middle line:90%
and the pandemic began?

00:02:20.490 --> 00:02:22.470 align:middle line:10%
>> NELSON: Well, I
think that, of course,

00:02:22.470 --> 00:02:25.470 align:middle line:10%
what's happening with people
is that they're being forced

00:02:25.470 --> 00:02:30.820 align:middle line:10%
into more isolation than
they've ever experienced before.

00:02:30.820 --> 00:02:32.610 align:middle line:84%
And we're not designed
to be isolated.

00:02:32.610 --> 00:02:35.220 align:middle line:90%
We're designed to be together.

00:02:35.220 --> 00:02:37.060 align:middle line:90%
We're not designed to be apart.

00:02:37.060 --> 00:02:39.570 align:middle line:84%
And so what that's
doing is it's creating

00:02:39.570 --> 00:02:42.460 align:middle line:84%
a lot of emotional baggage
for a lot of people.

00:02:42.460 --> 00:02:48.690 align:middle line:84%
And of course, when you
experience intense emotions,

00:02:48.690 --> 00:02:50.970 align:middle line:84%
those emotions sometimes
if they're too powerful

00:02:50.970 --> 00:02:53.730 align:middle line:84%
or if you have a tendency
to bury those emotions

00:02:53.730 --> 00:02:55.800 align:middle line:84%
and not want to feel
them, then those energies

00:02:55.800 --> 00:02:57.400 align:middle line:90%
can become trapped in the body.

00:02:57.400 --> 00:02:57.640 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:02:57.640 --> 00:02:59.550 align:middle line:84%
>> NELSON: And of course,
those are trapped emotions--

00:02:59.550 --> 00:03:00.930 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And we're
going to get into that.

00:03:00.930 --> 00:03:02.040 align:middle line:90%
>> NELSON: Yeah.

00:03:02.040 --> 00:03:05.580 align:middle line:84%
What we find is that
there are more people now

00:03:05.580 --> 00:03:08.970 align:middle line:84%
that seem to be forming
what we call a heart wall.

00:03:08.970 --> 00:03:10.853 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Interesting,
explain that.

00:03:10.853 --> 00:03:12.270 align:middle line:84%
We talked about
it in another show

00:03:12.270 --> 00:03:14.220 align:middle line:84%
but now that is
becoming so prominent,

00:03:14.220 --> 00:03:15.810 align:middle line:84%
let's give it center
stage for a bit.

00:03:15.810 --> 00:03:17.460 align:middle line:90%
>> NELSON: Well, what happens--

00:03:17.460 --> 00:03:19.997 align:middle line:84%
of course, the heart itself
is the seed of the soul

00:03:19.997 --> 00:03:22.080 align:middle line:84%
and the source of love and
creativity and romance.

00:03:22.080 --> 00:03:24.960 align:middle line:84%
Everything the ancient
peoples believed it to be.

00:03:24.960 --> 00:03:27.540 align:middle line:84%
And in modern science,
they're starting

00:03:27.540 --> 00:03:29.880 align:middle line:84%
to show now that the heart
really truly is a brain.

00:03:29.880 --> 00:03:31.750 align:middle line:90%
It's mostly nervous tissue.

00:03:31.750 --> 00:03:35.250 align:middle line:84%
Most of the messages between
the brain and the heart

00:03:35.250 --> 00:03:37.078 align:middle line:84%
are going from the
heart to the brain.

00:03:37.078 --> 00:03:39.120 align:middle line:84%
Instead of they thought
it would be the opposite.

00:03:39.120 --> 00:03:39.920 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:03:39.920 --> 00:03:43.170 align:middle line:84%
>> NELSON: And so what happens
to us is that when we feel like

00:03:43.170 --> 00:03:45.540 align:middle line:84%
our heart is going to break
or when things are really

00:03:45.540 --> 00:03:49.717 align:middle line:84%
difficult or we're in a very
insecure sort of situation

00:03:49.717 --> 00:03:52.050 align:middle line:84%
and things are going on like
what we've been seeing over

00:03:52.050 --> 00:03:57.600 align:middle line:84%
the last year or so, then it's
a situation where the heart can

00:03:57.600 --> 00:03:59.830 align:middle line:90%
feel like it's in danger.

00:03:59.830 --> 00:04:01.740 align:middle line:84%
And especially, this
happens if you feel

00:04:01.740 --> 00:04:03.155 align:middle line:90%
like your heart is breaking.

00:04:03.155 --> 00:04:04.530 align:middle line:84%
If you're going
through a breakup

00:04:04.530 --> 00:04:07.890 align:middle line:84%
or if you are really deeply
grieved or deeply hurt,

00:04:07.890 --> 00:04:10.950 align:middle line:84%
you can feel those physical
sensations like your heart

00:04:10.950 --> 00:04:12.360 align:middle line:90%
is actually going to break.

00:04:12.360 --> 00:04:15.990 align:middle line:84%
When that's going on,
the heart will put up

00:04:15.990 --> 00:04:18.308 align:middle line:90%
a wall around itself.

00:04:18.308 --> 00:04:20.850 align:middle line:84%
I believe the heart is actually
the seed of the subconscious,

00:04:20.850 --> 00:04:21.650 align:middle line:90%
really.

00:04:21.650 --> 00:04:24.900 align:middle line:84%
And it will put up a wall
around itself made of layers

00:04:24.900 --> 00:04:27.190 align:middle line:90%
of your emotional baggage.

00:04:27.190 --> 00:04:30.750 align:middle line:84%
And that's a protection
to protect the deepest

00:04:30.750 --> 00:04:33.220 align:middle line:90%
core of who you are.

00:04:33.220 --> 00:04:36.100 align:middle line:84%
And the problem
with that, though,

00:04:36.100 --> 00:04:38.760 align:middle line:84%
is that even though it might
be great in the short term,

00:04:38.760 --> 00:04:40.260 align:middle line:84%
and when the bombs
are falling, it's

00:04:40.260 --> 00:04:42.630 align:middle line:84%
kind of like moving your
heart into a bunker.

00:04:42.630 --> 00:04:47.100 align:middle line:84%
But the problem is when
things start to normalize,

00:04:47.100 --> 00:04:50.550 align:middle line:84%
now your heart is still
living in this bunker

00:04:50.550 --> 00:04:52.680 align:middle line:84%
and you've got this
wall around your heart.

00:04:52.680 --> 00:04:55.770 align:middle line:84%
And you see, when people
feel love or affection

00:04:55.770 --> 00:04:58.470 align:middle line:84%
for each other,
there's an energy

00:04:58.470 --> 00:05:01.620 align:middle line:84%
that travels from their heart
to that other person's heart.

00:05:01.620 --> 00:05:04.530 align:middle line:84%
And the problem is when
you have a heart wall,

00:05:04.530 --> 00:05:09.310 align:middle line:84%
that energy, the passage of
that energy is interfered with.

00:05:09.310 --> 00:05:12.330 align:middle line:84%
And so it makes it much harder
for you to give and receive

00:05:12.330 --> 00:05:16.830 align:middle line:84%
love, harder to really create
the perfect creation that I

00:05:16.830 --> 00:05:19.720 align:middle line:84%
think is in the heart, and
that subconscious mind.

00:05:19.720 --> 00:05:21.690 align:middle line:84%
And so in that
wall is taken down,

00:05:21.690 --> 00:05:24.720 align:middle line:84%
we've seen suicidally depressed
people get well in days

00:05:24.720 --> 00:05:26.340 align:middle line:84%
from having that
wall taken down.

00:05:26.340 --> 00:05:28.465 align:middle line:84%
I believe it's the most
important thing that people

00:05:28.465 --> 00:05:29.980 align:middle line:90%
can do for themselves.

00:05:29.980 --> 00:05:34.290 align:middle line:84%
I think that what we have to
get back to, really, is love

00:05:34.290 --> 00:05:36.120 align:middle line:90%
and unconditional love.

00:05:36.120 --> 00:05:38.610 align:middle line:84%
And unconditional
love basically says

00:05:38.610 --> 00:05:41.640 align:middle line:84%
that when you're feeling
it, you don't really

00:05:41.640 --> 00:05:47.310 align:middle line:84%
care whether somebody
is broke or homeless

00:05:47.310 --> 00:05:50.400 align:middle line:84%
or whether they have a different
political view than you

00:05:50.400 --> 00:05:53.610 align:middle line:84%
or whether they have a
different gender than you,

00:05:53.610 --> 00:05:57.300 align:middle line:84%
it's all about loving
people unconditionally.

00:05:57.300 --> 00:05:59.610 align:middle line:84%
And I think that that
is what it ultimately

00:05:59.610 --> 00:06:01.770 align:middle line:84%
is going to save the
world and what we need

00:06:01.770 --> 00:06:03.870 align:middle line:90%
to move towards, all of us.

00:06:03.870 --> 00:06:07.680 align:middle line:84%
The fascinating thing
about taking down

00:06:07.680 --> 00:06:11.040 align:middle line:84%
the wall around the heart
is that oftentimes people

00:06:11.040 --> 00:06:14.520 align:middle line:84%
fall in love even at
advanced stages that

00:06:14.520 --> 00:06:16.020 align:middle line:90%
never thought they would.

00:06:16.020 --> 00:06:19.350 align:middle line:84%
People find that they
can feel the love

00:06:19.350 --> 00:06:22.020 align:middle line:84%
of the creator, the higher power
for them when they could never

00:06:22.020 --> 00:06:23.490 align:middle line:90%
feel it before.

00:06:23.490 --> 00:06:25.260 align:middle line:90%
And in fact, I've got--

00:06:25.260 --> 00:06:27.770 align:middle line:84%
I have a story I can share
with you really quickly.

00:06:27.770 --> 00:06:29.730 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Oh, do.

00:06:29.730 --> 00:06:32.700 align:middle line:84%
>> NELSON: This is a man named
Giacomo Ravelli in London.

00:06:32.700 --> 00:06:35.310 align:middle line:84%
He said, after my heart
wall was released,

00:06:35.310 --> 00:06:37.500 align:middle line:90%
my life completely changed.

00:06:37.500 --> 00:06:39.510 align:middle line:84%
I became far more
open to the divine

00:06:39.510 --> 00:06:41.620 align:middle line:90%
and I started lucid dreaming.

00:06:41.620 --> 00:06:42.420 align:middle line:90%
This is cool.

00:06:42.420 --> 00:06:43.837 align:middle line:84%
After a few months,
I entered into

00:06:43.837 --> 00:06:46.590 align:middle line:84%
my first long-term relationship
with an amazing partner

00:06:46.590 --> 00:06:47.858 align:middle line:90%
in which I am very happy.

00:06:47.858 --> 00:06:50.400 align:middle line:84%
At first, I thought I wanted to
pursue a completely different

00:06:50.400 --> 00:06:51.300 align:middle line:90%
profession.

00:06:51.300 --> 00:06:53.950 align:middle line:84%
But after one month, my
resolve for my current passion

00:06:53.950 --> 00:06:57.040 align:middle line:84%
strengthened and I'm achieving
better results than ever in it.

00:06:57.040 --> 00:06:59.040 align:middle line:84%
I'm so grateful that I
discovered the heart wall

00:06:59.040 --> 00:07:00.150 align:middle line:90%
and had it released.

00:07:00.150 --> 00:07:04.740 align:middle line:84%
93% of people in this world
have this phenomenon going on.

00:07:04.740 --> 00:07:06.210 align:middle line:90%
This heart wall phenomenon.

00:07:06.210 --> 00:07:08.760 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Now, let's go into
this because we now have all

00:07:08.760 --> 00:07:13.110 align:middle line:84%
this stuff, this whole
new body of challenge kind

00:07:13.110 --> 00:07:17.520 align:middle line:84%
of that's been inculcated into
our fear base and into the deep

00:07:17.520 --> 00:07:19.690 align:middle line:84%
memory, the subconscious,
and so forth.

00:07:19.690 --> 00:07:22.890 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about how you start
working with people when they

00:07:22.890 --> 00:07:25.470 align:middle line:84%
have this kind of mass mental
trauma and someone comes to you

00:07:25.470 --> 00:07:28.140 align:middle line:84%
and says, I can't talk
to my family anymore.

00:07:28.140 --> 00:07:29.760 align:middle line:90%
I am so depressed.

00:07:29.760 --> 00:07:32.040 align:middle line:84%
Where do you begin
with them now?

00:07:32.040 --> 00:07:34.470 align:middle line:84%
>> NELSON: Well,
think about a glass.

00:07:34.470 --> 00:07:36.180 align:middle line:90%
We'll use this cup.

00:07:36.180 --> 00:07:40.170 align:middle line:84%
And let's imagine that this
cup is your being, your energy

00:07:40.170 --> 00:07:42.000 align:middle line:90%
body, your physical body.

00:07:42.000 --> 00:07:45.450 align:middle line:84%
And let's imagine that that cup
has emotional baggage in it.

00:07:45.450 --> 00:07:47.490 align:middle line:84%
And that emotional
baggage, some of it

00:07:47.490 --> 00:07:49.643 align:middle line:84%
is from when you
were a kid and used

00:07:49.643 --> 00:07:51.060 align:middle line:84%
to cry yourself
to sleep at night.

00:07:51.060 --> 00:07:52.768 align:middle line:84%
Some of it is from
when your parents were

00:07:52.768 --> 00:07:53.963 align:middle line:90%
arguing when you were young.

00:07:53.963 --> 00:07:55.380 align:middle line:84%
Some of it is the
break up you had

00:07:55.380 --> 00:07:56.880 align:middle line:90%
in junior high in high school.

00:07:56.880 --> 00:07:59.430 align:middle line:84%
Some of it is the divorce
that you went through.

00:07:59.430 --> 00:08:01.355 align:middle line:84%
Some of it is the
bad work situation

00:08:01.355 --> 00:08:02.730 align:middle line:84%
that you went
through, and so on.

00:08:02.730 --> 00:08:05.220 align:middle line:84%
And so what happens
is most people

00:08:05.220 --> 00:08:09.600 align:middle line:84%
have a cup that is most
of the way full already

00:08:09.600 --> 00:08:11.550 align:middle line:90%
with emotional baggage.

00:08:11.550 --> 00:08:14.400 align:middle line:90%
And a pandemic comes along.

00:08:14.400 --> 00:08:16.830 align:middle line:84%
And then all of this political
intrigue and everything

00:08:16.830 --> 00:08:17.790 align:middle line:90%
comes along.

00:08:17.790 --> 00:08:20.280 align:middle line:84%
And the problem is
there's no place

00:08:20.280 --> 00:08:22.830 align:middle line:84%
for that emotional
baggage now to really go,

00:08:22.830 --> 00:08:24.480 align:middle line:90%
and so it starts to overflow.

00:08:24.480 --> 00:08:28.030 align:middle line:84%
And people then
can't deal with life.

00:08:28.030 --> 00:08:33.870 align:middle line:84%
And so what we do is we start to
remove their emotional baggage

00:08:33.870 --> 00:08:37.440 align:middle line:84%
so that instead of their cup
running over all the time,

00:08:37.440 --> 00:08:39.659 align:middle line:84%
now they're creating
room so that they

00:08:39.659 --> 00:08:42.870 align:middle line:84%
can deal with the new emotional
stuff that's coming on.

00:08:42.870 --> 00:08:45.810 align:middle line:84%
And of course, in The Emotion
Code also in the last chapter,

00:08:45.810 --> 00:08:49.060 align:middle line:84%
we teach people how to
deal with emotional stuff

00:08:49.060 --> 00:08:52.290 align:middle line:84%
so that they're not so prone to
develop new emotional baggage.

00:08:52.290 --> 00:08:54.540 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Well, why don't
we talk about that for just

00:08:54.540 --> 00:08:54.870 align:middle line:90%
a moment?

00:08:54.870 --> 00:08:57.495 align:middle line:84%
Then we'll get into the nuts and
bolts of fixing it once you've

00:08:57.495 --> 00:08:58.410 align:middle line:90%
let it get in there.

00:08:58.410 --> 00:08:59.010 align:middle line:90%
>> NELSON: OK.

00:08:59.010 --> 00:09:01.552 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Want to talk about
that last chapter for a minute?

00:09:01.552 --> 00:09:04.050 align:middle line:90%
>> NELSON: Well, absolutely.

00:09:04.050 --> 00:09:06.270 align:middle line:84%
We talk about love
in that chapter,

00:09:06.270 --> 00:09:09.090 align:middle line:84%
and we talk about the
importance of feeling love

00:09:09.090 --> 00:09:11.850 align:middle line:90%
and how important it is to--

00:09:11.850 --> 00:09:15.630 align:middle line:84%
and how shifting it can
be for your own energy

00:09:15.630 --> 00:09:18.000 align:middle line:84%
to just tell people
that you love them.

00:09:18.000 --> 00:09:20.550 align:middle line:84%
And when you tell someone
that you love them, really

00:09:20.550 --> 00:09:25.560 align:middle line:84%
from your heart, and
anyone can do this,

00:09:25.560 --> 00:09:28.530 align:middle line:84%
even if you're not
saying it out loud,

00:09:28.530 --> 00:09:31.320 align:middle line:84%
your heart sends that energy to
them, their heart picks that up

00:09:31.320 --> 00:09:34.650 align:middle line:84%
and it understands that
on a subconscious level.

00:09:34.650 --> 00:09:36.930 align:middle line:90%
Practical example.

00:09:36.930 --> 00:09:40.590 align:middle line:84%
Recently, my wife and I
were shopping at Costco.

00:09:40.590 --> 00:09:44.440 align:middle line:84%
And you could feel the
panic in everybody.

00:09:44.440 --> 00:09:45.690 align:middle line:90%
I don't know, I think it was--

00:09:45.690 --> 00:09:46.590 align:middle line:90%
there was something going on.

00:09:46.590 --> 00:09:48.465 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: --people
filling up the carts at 9

00:09:48.465 --> 00:09:50.415 align:middle line:90%
o'clock in the morning.

00:09:50.415 --> 00:09:51.750 align:middle line:90%
>> NELSON: Exactly.

00:09:51.750 --> 00:09:53.353 align:middle line:90%
And I could feel the panic.

00:09:53.353 --> 00:09:55.770 align:middle line:84%
Everybody, people are zooming
around faster than I've ever

00:09:55.770 --> 00:09:58.770 align:middle line:84%
seen them go in
their carts and it

00:09:58.770 --> 00:10:01.260 align:middle line:84%
started to be-- it's an energy
that everybody's giving off

00:10:01.260 --> 00:10:02.627 align:middle line:90%
and I'm starting to absorb that.

00:10:02.627 --> 00:10:03.960 align:middle line:90%
And I'm starting to feel it too.

00:10:03.960 --> 00:10:07.030 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, wait a minute,
I don't want to go there.

00:10:07.030 --> 00:10:09.690 align:middle line:84%
So what I did is I just started
to tell people, people that I

00:10:09.690 --> 00:10:13.122 align:middle line:84%
have no idea who they
are, no connection at all,

00:10:13.122 --> 00:10:14.580 align:middle line:84%
I just started
telling them, I just

00:10:14.580 --> 00:10:18.660 align:middle line:84%
look at it them for a moment and
say, I love you just silently.

00:10:18.660 --> 00:10:19.770 align:middle line:90%
I love you.

00:10:19.770 --> 00:10:25.530 align:middle line:84%
And I'm telling you,
within 10 people, I was--

00:10:25.530 --> 00:10:27.300 align:middle line:84%
I'm sure I was the
highest vibration

00:10:27.300 --> 00:10:29.190 align:middle line:90%
person in the whole place.

00:10:29.190 --> 00:10:30.380 align:middle line:90%
Anybody can do this.

00:10:30.380 --> 00:10:33.210 align:middle line:84%
It's amazing how powerful
it is and how easily

00:10:33.210 --> 00:10:35.190 align:middle line:84%
and how quickly it
can shift your energy.

00:10:35.190 --> 00:10:36.810 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Absolutely.

00:10:36.810 --> 00:10:38.830 align:middle line:84%
>> NELSON: So that's
a great technique.

00:10:38.830 --> 00:10:43.120 align:middle line:84%
One of the other things that
we talk about in the book

00:10:43.120 --> 00:10:46.880 align:middle line:90%
at the very end is forgiveness.

00:10:46.880 --> 00:10:51.220 align:middle line:84%
Because when people do
things that hurt others

00:10:51.220 --> 00:10:53.710 align:middle line:84%
or when people do
things that hurt us,

00:10:53.710 --> 00:10:57.230 align:middle line:84%
the natural human tendency
is to withhold forgiveness,

00:10:57.230 --> 00:10:59.980 align:middle line:84%
because we want to get
even with that person.

00:10:59.980 --> 00:11:02.950 align:middle line:84%
And we're only
hurting ourselves.

00:11:02.950 --> 00:11:05.710 align:middle line:84%
Lewis Smedes said
that, "forgiveness

00:11:05.710 --> 00:11:09.370 align:middle line:84%
is like letting the prisoner
go free only to find out

00:11:09.370 --> 00:11:12.370 align:middle line:90%
that the prisoner was you."

00:11:12.370 --> 00:11:14.980 align:middle line:84%
And so if there are
people in your life

00:11:14.980 --> 00:11:18.640 align:middle line:84%
that you need to forgive,
you need to forgive them.

00:11:18.640 --> 00:11:21.070 align:middle line:90%
Let it go.

00:11:21.070 --> 00:11:22.570 align:middle line:84%
And I know that
some people believe

00:11:22.570 --> 00:11:26.890 align:middle line:84%
that it's enough to just become
indifferent to what they did

00:11:26.890 --> 00:11:29.650 align:middle line:90%
to you or indifferent to them.

00:11:29.650 --> 00:11:30.740 align:middle line:90%
But I don't believe that.

00:11:30.740 --> 00:11:32.380 align:middle line:90%
I think that you really truly--

00:11:32.380 --> 00:11:35.110 align:middle line:84%
to really have peace
in your own life,

00:11:35.110 --> 00:11:39.190 align:middle line:84%
you'll never have it
until you forgive.

00:11:39.190 --> 00:11:42.170 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes you need
to forgive yourself.

00:11:42.170 --> 00:11:44.835 align:middle line:84%
And that's the person that
needs it the most sometimes.

00:11:44.835 --> 00:11:45.710 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Very true.

00:11:45.710 --> 00:11:48.610 align:middle line:84%
And as you're
speaking these words,

00:11:48.610 --> 00:11:50.740 align:middle line:84%
I've always had an
odd relationship--

00:11:50.740 --> 00:11:53.020 align:middle line:84%
and I know my husband's
called me on it, he said,

00:11:53.020 --> 00:11:54.940 align:middle line:84%
you don't believe
in forgiveness?

00:11:54.940 --> 00:11:58.750 align:middle line:84%
And I said, I don't in the
classic sense of the word

00:11:58.750 --> 00:12:03.970 align:middle line:84%
because the way my being
works is what I do instead

00:12:03.970 --> 00:12:08.140 align:middle line:84%
is I go into and try to walk
in their shoes emotionally

00:12:08.140 --> 00:12:12.280 align:middle line:84%
and understand, really try to
understand what the factors are

00:12:12.280 --> 00:12:15.520 align:middle line:84%
in their life that would
take them to that point,

00:12:15.520 --> 00:12:18.310 align:middle line:84%
to do the thing that was
hurtful or painful or whatever.

00:12:18.310 --> 00:12:20.860 align:middle line:84%
And I find that
no forgiveness is

00:12:20.860 --> 00:12:24.400 align:middle line:84%
needed if you can
understand why someone was

00:12:24.400 --> 00:12:25.820 align:middle line:90%
motivated to do what they do.

00:12:25.820 --> 00:12:28.210 align:middle line:84%
And I think to take the
time to really understand

00:12:28.210 --> 00:12:31.210 align:middle line:84%
another person or the
classic walk a mile

00:12:31.210 --> 00:12:33.940 align:middle line:84%
in someone else's shoes
is really critical

00:12:33.940 --> 00:12:36.460 align:middle line:84%
and it almost eliminates
the need to even have

00:12:36.460 --> 00:12:37.840 align:middle line:90%
to go through any forgiveness.

00:12:37.840 --> 00:12:39.400 align:middle line:90%
It's understood.

00:12:39.400 --> 00:12:40.600 align:middle line:90%
It's understanding.

00:12:40.600 --> 00:12:42.492 align:middle line:90%
>> NELSON: That's a great point.

00:12:42.492 --> 00:12:44.950 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And everyone has to
decide how they want to deal

00:12:44.950 --> 00:12:48.160 align:middle line:84%
with it because a lot of times,
forgiveness is I'm holding this

00:12:48.160 --> 00:12:50.710 align:middle line:90%
over you but I forgive you.

00:12:50.710 --> 00:12:54.560 align:middle line:84%
There's something
missing in that for me.

00:12:54.560 --> 00:12:55.360 align:middle line:90%
>> NELSON: Yeah.

00:12:55.360 --> 00:12:58.060 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: I would rather
understand the person.

00:12:58.060 --> 00:13:00.430 align:middle line:84%
>> NELSON: I think that's
absolutely important

00:13:00.430 --> 00:13:03.070 align:middle line:84%
because if you can understand
what caused them to do

00:13:03.070 --> 00:13:05.970 align:middle line:90%
the things that they did, then--

00:13:05.970 --> 00:13:07.350 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: A reaction comes out.

00:13:07.350 --> 00:13:09.093 align:middle line:90%
>> NELSON: Well, exactly.

00:13:09.093 --> 00:13:10.510 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes we need
help to forgive.

00:13:10.510 --> 00:13:12.010 align:middle line:90%
I mean, sometimes--

00:13:12.010 --> 00:13:14.530 align:middle line:84%
I had a situation in
my life where I was--

00:13:14.530 --> 00:13:19.480 align:middle line:84%
I felt very wronged by some
people that were close to me.

00:13:19.480 --> 00:13:22.510 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't feel
like I would ever

00:13:22.510 --> 00:13:27.200 align:middle line:84%
be able to associate
with them again.

00:13:27.200 --> 00:13:31.290 align:middle line:84%
and I felt like it was beyond my
ability to be able to forgive.

00:13:31.290 --> 00:13:34.270 align:middle line:84%
And so what I did is I gave
it back to the higher power,

00:13:34.270 --> 00:13:36.460 align:middle line:84%
and I said, God, if
you want me to be

00:13:36.460 --> 00:13:39.340 align:middle line:84%
able to work with these
people in the future,

00:13:39.340 --> 00:13:43.720 align:middle line:84%
you're going to need to help me
to forgive them because I'm not

00:13:43.720 --> 00:13:44.930 align:middle line:90%
able to do it on my own.

00:13:44.930 --> 00:13:46.130 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't do it.

00:13:46.130 --> 00:13:48.530 align:middle line:90%
And it was a fascinating thing.

00:13:48.530 --> 00:13:51.100 align:middle line:84%
I offered that prayer
about three times.

00:13:51.100 --> 00:13:53.740 align:middle line:84%
And on the morning of
the third day, I woke up

00:13:53.740 --> 00:13:55.410 align:middle line:90%
and it was all gone.

00:13:55.410 --> 00:13:57.362 align:middle line:84%
And God had just taken
it out of my being.

00:13:57.362 --> 00:13:59.320 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Well, there
you go and that's grace.

00:13:59.320 --> 00:14:02.980 align:middle line:84%
Because to continue
this thought,

00:14:02.980 --> 00:14:05.860 align:middle line:84%
there are things people
do that are self-motivated

00:14:05.860 --> 00:14:07.910 align:middle line:84%
and just pure
greed, for example.

00:14:07.910 --> 00:14:12.550 align:middle line:84%
People will screw each other
out over for greedy purposes

00:14:12.550 --> 00:14:14.107 align:middle line:90%
which is not acceptable.

00:14:14.107 --> 00:14:16.690 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there's no way to kind
of look at that and justify it.

00:14:16.690 --> 00:14:19.390 align:middle line:84%
You could say, OK, maybe you
didn't have enough growing up.

00:14:19.390 --> 00:14:22.760 align:middle line:84%
And I mean, I'm kind of
contradicting myself now here.

00:14:22.760 --> 00:14:24.610 align:middle line:84%
And then beyond
that, if you think,

00:14:24.610 --> 00:14:26.110 align:middle line:84%
God, I've looked
at this every way.

00:14:26.110 --> 00:14:28.430 align:middle line:84%
That's just greed
and that's not fair.

00:14:28.430 --> 00:14:29.980 align:middle line:84%
And then the way
I'd go about it is,

00:14:29.980 --> 00:14:33.580 align:middle line:84%
I want to talk to that
person and reconcile this.

00:14:33.580 --> 00:14:35.950 align:middle line:84%
And you can't always
get reconciliation

00:14:35.950 --> 00:14:39.610 align:middle line:84%
because that person may not
feel that they're necessarily

00:14:39.610 --> 00:14:42.620 align:middle line:84%
operating out of greed or
selfishness or whatnot.

00:14:42.620 --> 00:14:45.100 align:middle line:84%
So they're not going
to see it in themselves

00:14:45.100 --> 00:14:50.490 align:middle line:84%
and you're not going to have
a reasonable conversation.

00:14:50.490 --> 00:14:53.990 align:middle line:84%
And that's where my way
of doing things absolutely

00:14:53.990 --> 00:14:57.680 align:middle line:84%
fails because you can't
truly understand why

00:14:57.680 --> 00:14:59.200 align:middle line:90%
someone would do these things.

00:14:59.200 --> 00:15:02.720 align:middle line:84%
So then that's where yours
comes in as very beautiful

00:15:02.720 --> 00:15:06.110 align:middle line:84%
and offering grace into the
situation when understanding

00:15:06.110 --> 00:15:06.942 align:middle line:90%
is impossible.

00:15:06.942 --> 00:15:08.900 align:middle line:84%
>> NELSON: Well, you know
the reality of it is,

00:15:08.900 --> 00:15:11.325 align:middle line:90%
we all need to be forgiven.

00:15:11.325 --> 00:15:12.950 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Yeah, we
all have our stuff.

00:15:12.950 --> 00:15:13.783 align:middle line:90%
>> NELSON: Don't we?

00:15:13.783 --> 00:15:16.100 align:middle line:84%
We all do things that
looking back that we regret.

00:15:16.100 --> 00:15:20.330 align:middle line:84%
We all do things that now we
wouldn't even think of doing

00:15:20.330 --> 00:15:22.760 align:middle line:84%
but that we did when
we were younger.

00:15:22.760 --> 00:15:25.370 align:middle line:84%
We all have things that
we need forgiveness for.

00:15:25.370 --> 00:15:31.250 align:middle line:84%
And so I mean, to me, that's
what helps me to motivate--

00:15:31.250 --> 00:15:34.550 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there but for the
grace of God go right.

00:15:34.550 --> 00:15:38.960 align:middle line:84%
I should forgive anybody
and everybody in my life

00:15:38.960 --> 00:15:40.918 align:middle line:90%
because I need that myself.

00:15:40.918 --> 00:15:41.960 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: And we all do.

00:15:41.960 --> 00:15:43.412 align:middle line:90%
We all need that grace.

00:15:43.412 --> 00:15:45.620 align:middle line:84%
We all need that grace where
we've lied to ourselves,

00:15:45.620 --> 00:15:47.930 align:middle line:84%
for example, and we've
hoodwinked ourselves

00:15:47.930 --> 00:15:50.570 align:middle line:84%
and justified things
in our own name.

00:15:50.570 --> 00:15:52.880 align:middle line:84%
So this is-- thank you for
bringing this last chapter

00:15:52.880 --> 00:15:53.450 align:middle line:90%
of the book up.

00:15:53.450 --> 00:15:55.490 align:middle line:84%
I think it's really important we
have this little conversation.

00:15:55.490 --> 00:15:56.782 align:middle line:90%
>> NELSON: It's a good chapter.

00:15:56.782 --> 00:15:57.650 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Good.

00:15:57.650 --> 00:16:01.220 align:middle line:84%
OK, now, let's go on to
working with the heart while

00:16:01.220 --> 00:16:02.420 align:middle line:90%
in particular right now.

00:16:02.420 --> 00:16:05.690 align:middle line:84%
What happens and how
one starts that process?

00:16:05.690 --> 00:16:08.070 align:middle line:90%
And what one can expect to see?

00:16:08.070 --> 00:16:10.250 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes when it
doesn't work so well, what

00:16:10.250 --> 00:16:12.870 align:middle line:90%
is going on there?

00:16:12.870 --> 00:16:15.390 align:middle line:84%
>> NELSON: Well, first
of all, of course,

00:16:15.390 --> 00:16:17.570 align:middle line:84%
